python -m venv .venv

Explanation:
python -m venv tells Python to execute the venv module for creating virtual environments.
.venv specifies the name of the virtual environment to be created in the current directory (you can choose another name).

Example:
python -m venv MyVirtualEnv  # Creates a virtual environment named MyVirtualEnv

Verification:
If successful, see output indicating of the virtual environment directory (.venv in this case).

Next Steps:
Now that the virtual environment exists, activate it using in the Command Prompt:
.\venv\Scripts\activate.bat  # Activate the virtual environment named .v

HOW TO ACTIVATE A VIRTUAL ENVIROMMENT:

